article.description: Marvelle Harris scored 20 points including a pair of free throws in the final four seconds that made the difference as Fresno State rallied late to beat Air Force 64-63 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Harris free throw puts Fresno State over of Air Force 64-63
article.linkText: Harris free throw puts Fresno State over of Air Force 64-63
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. -- Marvelle Harris scored 20 points including a pair of free throws in the final four seconds that made the difference as Fresno State rallied late to beat Air Force 64-63 on Wednesday night. With Air Force leading 63-60, Harris hit two free throws to close it to 63-62 with 40 seconds to go. With four seconds left, Harris was back at the line again where he drained two more for the win. Harris was 6 of 13 from the field and hit all five of his free throws for the Bulldogs (19-9, 10-5 Mountain West Conference). He scored 18 points in the second half and had four steals and three blocks. Karachi Edo added 12 points. Zach Kocur scored 19 points for the Falcons (14-15, 5-11). Hayden Graham and Jacob Van added 11 points each. The Falcons led through most of the game until Harris tied it up, 63-63, before sinking the winning point.
